HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1199
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Lieutenant Billy Atwell
upon his receipt of the 2025 Leader of the Year
award.
WHEREAS, our nation was conceived by individuals who were willing to sacrifice their
personal concerns to ensure the public safety and welfare, and the Volunteer State is especially
proud to be the home of so many valiant individuals who have performed above and beyond the
call of duty in service of public safety; and
WHEREAS, Lieutenant Billy Atwell is one such individual, who was recently honored
with the Leader of the Year award by the Chattanooga Police Department in recognition of his
exemplary leadership daily, as well as during serious times of need or crisis; and
WHEREAS, Lieutenant Atwell shows consistent dedication and integrity through his
tireless efforts, often working late to implement initiatives that bolster the entire department; and
WHEREAS, holding himself to the highest standards, Lieutenant Billy Atwell consistently
meets expectations, which enables him to effectively hold others accountable to their roles and
responsibilities; and
WHEREAS, the support and commitment provided by Lieutenant Atwell has made a
lasting impact on the Chattanooga Police Department; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Lieutenant Billy Atwell upon his receipt of the
Leader of the Year award from the Chattanooga Police Department.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
